modules.description: This module implements password-based key derivation functions PBKDF1 and PBKDF2 using a provided hash function. It takes a password, salt, iteration count, and desired key length to produce a derived key. It works with strings for password and salt, integers for iteration count and key length, and relies on the provided hash module for cryptographic operations. Use this to securely derive encryption keys from user passwords for storage or cryptographic protocols.

This module implements PBKDF1 and PBKDF2 key derivation algorithms using a specified hash function. It operates on strings for passwords and salts, integers for iteration counts and key lengths, and produces derived keys as strings. It is used to securely generate cryptographic keys from user passwords for encryption or authentication purposes.
